        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 5:44AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 543 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms stretching from northeastern Jones County into
southeastern Haskell, to eastern Throckmorton County. Movement was
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lueders, Mccarty Lake, Stamford, Lusk, Throckmorton, Paint Creek,
Ibex, Nugent, Avoca, Woodson, Big Country Baptist Assembly, Lake
Stamford Marina, Fort Griffin, and Albany.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
